<TITLE> President XI lose another </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  The President XI Bangladesh suffered their second consecutive defeat in the 45th Jindal Steel Nehru Hockey Tournament with a 5-3 loss to South Central Railway in Haryana, India on Friday. The President XI, comprised of Bangladesh national players, went ahead in the 14th minute when Sheikh Mohammad Nannu converted a penalty corner, but the lead lasted only two minutes. Mayur Subbajah levelled for Railway also from a penalty corner in the 16th minute before Prabhakar Singh made it 2-1 in the 33rd minute. After resumption, Railway widened their lead to 3-1 with the help of second goal from Subbajah two minutes into the second half. Nannu then pulled one back in the 48th minute. Three minutes later Subbajah converted his third corner and Amit Srrivas made it 5-2 five minutes later to take the match away from the President XI. Rimon Kumar Ghosh struck in the 61st minute to reduce the margin for the President XI, who lost their first game 5-1 to Bharat Petroleum. The visitors will take on ONGC XI in their group-last match on Sunday. b
